--------------------------------------------------------------------------
def: ^relationship
is: ^symbol
doc: "Supertype for tags which model relationships"
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
def: ^inverseOf
is: ^symbol
doc: "Specifies the inverse of a relationship"
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
def: ^transitive
is: ^marker
doc:
  This marker is applied to a `relationship` to indicate it is transitive.
  Transitivity requires that if the relationship applies to A,B and B,C
  then it also applies to A,C.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
// Contains/ContainedBy
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
def: ^contains
is: ^relationship
inverseOf: ^containedBy
transitive
doc: "The entity is contained by the referent"
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
def: ^containedBy
is: ^relationship
inverseOf: ^contains
transitive
doc: "The entity contains the referent"
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
// Receives/Supplies
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
def: ^receives
is: ^relationship
inverseOf: ^supplies
doc:
  The entity receives from the referent.
  The value of this tag is what is received.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
def: ^supplies
is: ^relationship
inverseOf: ^receives
transitive
doc:
  The entity supplies to the referent.
  The value of this tag is what is supplied.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------


